title: Bicyclist Dies Nearly A Week After Crash
text:
Bicyclist Dies Nearly A Week After Crash October 15, 2015, 10:50 AM SIOUX FALLS, SD - 
A bicyclist hurt in a crash a week ago has died. 
Sioux Falls Police confirmed the death of the 63-year-old man on Thursday. They have not released his name yet. 
The crash happened last Thursday evening. Police say a 56-year-old woman was trying to leave a gas station parking lot on 41st Street near the Empire Mall. With a break in traffic, Clemens said the driver looked east but did not check to the west. 
The bicyclist struck the front right tire of the 2011 Toyota Camry and was thrown from his bicycle. The man was wearing a helmet and travelling about 5 miles per hour at the time of the crash, the car's speed is unknown. 
The woman was given two citations following the crash: failure to yield from a private drive and failure to exercise due care. Police say the State's Attorney's office is considering additional charges now that the bicyclist has died. Â© 2015 KELOLAND TV. All Rights Reserved.
